00160 /* Copy COUNT objects from FROM to TO.  The source and destination do
00161    not overlap.  */
00162 # ifndef YYCOPY

00165       __builtin_memcpy (To, From, (Count) * sizeof (*(From)))
00166 #  else
00167 #   define YYCOPY(To, From, Count)              \
00168       do                                        \
00169         {                                       \
00170           register YYSIZE_T yyi;                \
00171           for (yyi = 0; yyi < (Count); yyi++)   \

00178 /* Relocate STACK from its old location to the new one.  The
00179    local variables YYSIZE and YYSTACKSIZE give the old and new number of
00180    elements in the stack, and YYPTR gives the new location of the
00181    stack.  Advance YYPTR to a properly aligned location for the next
00182    stack.  */
00183 # define YYSTACK_RELOCATE(Stack)                                        \
00184     do                                                                  \
00185       {                                                                 \
00186         YYSIZE_T yynewbytes;                                            \
00187         YYCOPY (&yyptr->Stack, Stack, yysize);                          \
00188         Stack = &yyptr->Stack;                                          \
00189         yynewbytes = yystacksize * sizeof (*Stack) + YYSTACK_GAP_MAXIMUM; \
00190         yyptr += yynewbytes / sizeof (*yyptr);                          \
00191       }                                                                 \
00192     while (0)

00194 #endif
